This paper proposes a method for face completion and editing using a deep learning approach. The paper focuses on facial geometry and uses a facial geometry estimator to estimate facial landmark heatmaps and parsing maps. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses an encoder-decoder structure generator, which is a common technique in deep learning for image generation and manipulation. This further supports the likelihood of the paper belonging to the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of low-rank regularization, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper's focus on facial attributes and editing suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper's use of geometry and landmarks suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on image completion and editing suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
